t-rex-converter (1.0.5-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Cosmetic fix: FieldLabel widgets (the bold caption above each form
    input on OCR / Subtitle / Audio Mix / Image Montage / etc panels)
    rendered with a thin teal box on Debian Trixie because the panel's
    QWidget cascade gave them a soft background that Qt's Fusion style
    then framed. Explicit border: 0; padding: 0; background:
    transparent on #FieldLabel removes the box.

 -- T-Rex Converter Maintainers <maintainers@example.invalid>  Wed, 07 May 2026 07:50:00 +0700

t-rex-converter (1.0.4-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix Check Dependencies dialog reporting "python:fitz: missing" on
    Debian Trixie. The PDFEngine declares requires_binary="python:fitz"
    but Debian python3-pymupdf 1.25 ships only `pymupdf` (legacy `fitz`
    alias removed). DependencyChecker now treats `fitz` and `pymupdf`
    as aliases of each other so either module satisfies the dep.

 -- T-Rex Converter Maintainers <maintainers@example.invalid>  Wed, 07 May 2026 07:00:00 +0700

t-rex-converter (1.0.3-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Critical fix: app crashed on launch with "TypeError: NoneType
    takes no arguments" because PySide6.QtCharts is shipped in a
    separate Debian package not pulled by python3-pyside6.qtwidgets.
    Add python3-pyside6.qtcharts and python3-pyside6.qtsvg + libqt6svg6
    (for SVG logo rendering) to Depends, and split the dashboard's
    QtCharts try/except so a missing QtCharts no longer nulls the
    QtWidgets imports it shares with QtCharts.
  * Dashboard chart tab now degrades gracefully with a placeholder
    label when QtCharts isn't installed instead of taking the whole
    app down.

 -- T-Rex Converter Maintainers <maintainers@example.invalid>  Wed, 07 May 2026 06:30:00 +0700

t-rex-converter (1.0.2-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix: Ignore on the optional-dependencies dialog now actually opens
    the main window. Previously the dialog created its own throwaway
    QApplication that conflicted with the second one created by main(),
    so after Ignore the app exited silently. main() now creates the
    QApplication once (after verifying required Python deps) and the
    dialog reuses it via QApplication.instance().

 -- T-Rex Converter Maintainers <maintainers@example.invalid>  Wed, 07 May 2026 06:00:00 +0700

t-rex-converter (1.0.1-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix PyMuPDF detection on Debian Trixie. python3-pymupdf 1.25 only
    ships the `pymupdf` import (the legacy `fitz` alias was removed),
    so the launch-time dep check and every `import fitz` in the engines
    now try `pymupdf` first and fall back to `fitz`. The dialog at
    launch no longer falsely reports PyMuPDF as missing on a fresh
    .deb install.
  * Fix broken logo on system install. assets/trex-logo.svg is now
    bundled at /usr/share/t-rex-converter/assets/, and the asset_path
    helper falls back to that location when the source-checkout layout
    is not present.

 -- T-Rex Converter Maintainers <maintainers@example.invalid>  Wed, 06 May 2026 16:52:56 +0700

t-rex-converter (1.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * 1.0 release. Roadmap fully closed across every module: Image,
    Video, Audio, Document, OCR, PDF Tools (DOCX, EPUB, A/B compare,
    split-by-size, image-downsample, linearize), Subtitle, Archive,
    QR, SVG / Vector (Wave 1+2+3), Ebook (Pandoc), Metadata (exiftool).
  * In-app documentation system: 31 topics x 2 languages (EN / ID)
    bundled as markdown via importlib.resources, with a sidebar
    mode-switch ("Need Help ?" entry), realtime QCompleter search,
    and a "?" button on every conversion page that jumps straight to
    the matching topic.
  * Smart launch-time dependency check: app/main.py now detects
    missing Python deps (PySide6, qasync, PyMuPDF, pdf2docx) and
    surfaces a clear Qt dialog with copy-pastable install commands
    instead of crashing or printing to a stderr the user never sees.
    If even PySide6 is missing, falls back to zenity / xmessage when
    available and finally to stderr.
  * postinst banner reformatted with a visible boxed summary listing
    every missing engine binary plus the pip command for the three
    Python deps not packaged in Debian apt (PyMuPDF, qasync, pdf2docx).

 -- T-Rex Converter Maintainers <maintainers@example.invalid>  Wed, 06 May 2026 16:16:05 +0700

t-rex-converter (0.4.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian packaging release with full module surface:
    Image (ImageMagick), Video / Audio (FFmpeg), Document (LibreOffice),
    PDF Tools (PyMuPDF + qpdf + pdf2docx), Subtitle (Python parser),
    OCR (Tesseract), Archive (Python stdlib), QR (qrencode + zbarimg),
    SVG / Vector (Inkscape + potrace), Ebook (Pandoc), Metadata
    (exiftool).
  * Recommends pulls in the optional engine binaries used by SVG,
    Ebook, Metadata, and QR modules.
  * postinst warns about any missing system engine and points at the
    pip install command for the three Python deps not packaged in
    Debian apt (PyMuPDF, qasync, pdf2docx).

 -- T-Rex Converter Maintainers <maintainers@example.invalid>  Wed, 06 May 2026 16:00:00 +0700
